- Wrapped all 15 mutation methods with try/catch rollback: `deleteToken`, `deleteTokens`, `createToken`, `updateToken`, `batchUpsertTokens`, `restoreSnapshot`, `renameGroup`, `renameToken`, `moveGroup`, `moveToken`, `copyToken`, `duplicateGroup`, `createGroup`, `updateGroup`, `bulkRename`
- For multi-set operations (renameToken, renameGroup with alias updates, moveGroup, moveToken, bulkRename), all potentially-modified sets are snapshotted before any mutation

